The characters of the Iranian population of
A. macrurus
agree with its description (
Geraert 2011
), except for extending the range of MB value ( 49–55 vs. 52–59 ). The morphologic and morphometric characters of the collected population of
A. paraglobigerus
from Iran fit well with the original description (
Castillo et al . 1990
), except in having a slightly longer stylet in females ( 21.5 –25.0 vs. 20–23 µm) and males ( 21.7 –23.0 vs. 20–22 µm), and in the ratio of isthmus to basal bulb length (1.0– 1.2 vs. 1.5 ). The morphometrics of the Iranian populations of
A. globigerus
are consistent with the original description (
Siddiqi 1976
), except in wider ranges for b , c , and c' indices, and stylet and spicule lengths (Table 2 ).

